   Contacting GSA

      If you have questions about GSA supplies or services, or you would like
      to make a request, please contact GSA Communications. GSA
      Communications will help you with your questions and requests or refer
      you to the appropriate office.

      If you represent a small business or a woman-owned or minority-owned
      business and you are interested in doing business with GSA, please
      contact the GSA Office of Enterprise Development .

      If you would like to report fraud, waste, or abuse involving GSA
      programs or personnel, contact the GSA Office of Inspector General or
      our Hotline.

      If you are having difficulty accessing GSA Advantage! (GSA's on-line
      shopping service), contact gsa.advantage@gsa.gov.

      If you have technical questions, comments, or suggestions, or would
      like to add information to the GSA site, contact the webmaster@gsa.gov.




